<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - ELECTRONIC GAUGE CLUSTER -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - EGC PRELIMINARY SYSTEM CHECK
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x08290020" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EGC PRELIMINARY SYSTEM CHECK</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Problems with EGC operation can be caused by a lack of power, a malfunctioning EGC, a malfunctioning
                ESC, a malfunctioning data link, incorrect or lost programming in the ESC, problems in the engine
                controller, problems in the ABS controller, problems in the transmission controller, or problems with
                wiring or sensors feeding the electronic controllers throughout the system.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>EGC Preliminary System Check</title>
            <para>The preliminary system check should guide the mechanic to a general area to start troubleshooting.
            </para>
            <table id="t08290027" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>EGC Preliminary System Check</title>
                <tgroup cols="6" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.53in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="1.30in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.70in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0" align="center">
